<title>USA: BP America sells U.S. headquarters building.</title>
<headline>BP America sells U.S. headquarters building.</headline>
<dateline>CLEVELAND 1996-09-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>BP America Inc said Thursday it sold its headquarters building here to Equity Office Holdings of Chicago for $145 million.</p>
<p>The building cost $200 million when it opened in 1985.</p>
<p>A BP America spokesman said parent company British Petroleum Co Plc had taken a charge in the second quarter to reflect the lower value of the building.</p>
<p>BP America, which occupies 25 percent of the 45-story office building, has signed a 12-year lease with the new owners, the spokesman added.</p>
<p>Reuters Chicago Newsdesk - 312-408-8787</p>
